item.description:
A confounding variable is a variable that influences both the explanatory variable and the response variable.
What does it mean when variables are confounded?
It is impossible to determine the extent of confounding. However, there are methods that we can use to minimize such effect:
  Restrict the treatment group by including subjects with same traits;
  Use matching by selecting two treatment groups, these two groups should have similar potential confounding variables but different independent variable values;
